use well, as was state...that group is very very mage biased.  Pet lost NO dps from lack of haste, the melees did.  Mages lose ALOT less mana regen from not having KEI then other classes do, because rods are a big part of our mana regen, specualy if you have more then 1 healer which this group did, AND was a dungeon crawl so medding wasn't as much of an option, so standing regen became even more important.  So really in my oppinion the numbers are out of wack a bit, but even in a balanced group a mage will outdamage most people, just not THAT largely.  We have *no* defensive spells and we wear cloth, noone should compaire to us in any circumstance really.  Don't know how many times its been said but, we pay for our offense with our defense, rogues can at least wear chain and have more hp/disciplines etc.<br>
<br>
I've read a bunch of times in this thread people saying &quot;A good mage always does this&quot; or a good mage always does that...Its so ignorent to make comments like that, who's to say one single play style is &quot;smart' and everything else is dumb?  For instance...I almost never have a rain or Scars memmed, yet apparently in this thread &quot;EVERY good mage&quot; has them memmed ALL the time...I have damn near 400 play days on my mage, i've seen almost everything in the game now...and ya know how many times I've said to myself, damn I wish I had a rain or scars memmed in the past 6 months?  None /shrug.  Maybe your doing something wrong if you need them?<br>
<br>
I don't think mages need any more enhancements really, I think we're pretty well balanced where we should be, unless these other classes continue to get repeated enhancements like they are right now...but totaly bias logs like this one will give the impression that we're more powerful then we are and yaknow, it could lead to nerfs, is that what we really want? <p>Sage Kalahad Thundersoul,
